defaultA defaultmdefaultisdefaultplaced loyalty and power are prioritised above truth and justice.default defaultPsychologists call this phenomenon, ‘Groupthink’.  It commonly unites bullying groups.  It is characterised by pressures to conform, 
defaultperceived 
defaultsafety in group membership, 
defaulta sense of power, 
defaultr
defaultationalised self justification,
default a belief in group unanimity, self censorship, belittlement of others
